OL,3,CBritain facing 'urgent crisis', major
OL,4,Creview into workplace sickness warns
OL,6,FAs part of his report, Mayfield
OL,7,Fproposed a new approach, where
OL,8,Fresponsibility for health at work is
OL,9,Fshared between employers, employees
OL,10,Fand health services rather than being
OL,11,Fleft to the worker and the NHS.
OL,13,FWhile he said employers must do more
OL,14,Fto help their employees, he warned
OL,15,Fthat workers must play their part,
OL,16,Fwriting: "Work can be demanding.
OL,17,FSetbacks are part of life. Health and
OL,18,Fwork are not always easy partners, but
OL,19,Fthey are mutually reinforcing."
